SUMMARY:Beginning 4 Shaft Weaving with Gale Hill & Karin Lauderback\, Day 1
DESCRIPTION:In this 3-day workshop\, students will learn the basics of loom weaving.  They will learn to measure a warp\, dress a loom and weave a chenille scarf. No previous weaving experience is necessary. \nSaturday and Sunday\, April 18\, 19\, & Saturday\, April 25\, 2026 12:00 – 5:00 PM \n$130.00 BSWG Members \n$140.00 Student non-members (includes one-year guild membership) \n$160.00 Non-members (includes one-year guild membership) \nClass size: 2-4 \nInstructors will email you regarding what you need to bring to class. \nALL SPOTS RESERVED – REGISTRATION CLOSED \n\n           Download QR
URL:https://bloomspinweave.org/event/beginning-4-shaft-weaving-with-gale-hill-karin-lauderback
CATEGORIES:Bloomington Spinners and Weavers Fiber Arts Guild Calendar
